<subSubSection id="909454EAFFADA479FF75FE5DFB576915" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D8310761FFADA479FF75FE5DFB576915" blockId="103.[151,1437,151,1365]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FF75FE5DFE886AF9" bold="true" box="[199,335,475,501]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FD8DFE5DFD456AF9" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kusnezov" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[575,642,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FD8DFE5DFD456AF9" box="[575,642,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was named for Cañadón León, 
<collectingRegion id="1A4AC983FFADA479FC58FE5DFB156AF9" box="[1002,1234,475,501]" country="Argentina" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Santa Cruz Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A09947F1FFADA479FB69FE5DFA8A6AF9" box="[1243,1357,475,501]" name="Argentina" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, where Kusnezov collected the 
<typeStatus id="0735B9C3FFADA479FE11FE79FE3D6915" box="[419,506,511,537]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">syntype</typeStatus>
series. Cañadón León is now called Gobernador Gregores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="909454EAFFADA479FF75FDA4FC436FC9" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D8310761FFADA479FF75FDA4FECA68C5" blockId="103.[151,1437,151,1365]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FF75FDA4FE8B6930" bold="true" box="[199,332,546,572]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FEE7FDA5FD976931" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kusnezov" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[341,592,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FEE7FDA5FD976931" box="[341,592,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Pogonomyrmex leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
likely co-occurs with 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FCFDFDA5FC226930" authorityName="Kusnezov. The" authorityYear="1953" box="[847,997,547,572]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanmartini">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FCFDFDA5FC226930" box="[847,997,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. sanmartini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FBACFDA5FB0B6931" baseAuthorityName="Snelling &amp; Hunt" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[1054,1228,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vermiculatus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FBACFDA5FB0B6931" box="[1054,1228,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. vermiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and possibly with 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FF25FDC1FEDB696D" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,284,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicolor">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FF25FDC1FEDB696D" box="[151,284,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. varicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FEEEFDC1FDC1696D" authorityName="Kusnezov" authorityYear="1951" box="[348,518,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FEEEFDC1FDC1696D" box="[348,518,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FDA7FDC1FCD7696D" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kusnezov" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[533,784,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FDA7FDC1FCD7696D" box="[533,784,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Pogonomyrmex leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from the first three species based on: (1) anterior portion of first gastral tergum moderately to strongly coriarious, rest of tergum smooth and shining, and (2) head ferruginous orange to orange-red; mesosoma, petiolar node, postpetiole blackish to black; gaster, legs orangish-brown to brownish-orange. 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FE49FD35FCEC69C0" authorityName="Kusnezov. The" authorityYear="1953" box="[507,811,691,716]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanmartini">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FE49FD35FCEC69C0" box="[507,811,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Pogonomyrmex sanmartini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FCD9FD35FC2869C1" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[875,1007,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicolor">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FCD9FD35FC2869C1" box="[875,1007,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. varicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have striae on the first gastral tergum and/or a different color pattern. 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FE4FFD51FC8269FD" baseAuthorityName="Snelling &amp; Hunt" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[509,837,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vermiculatus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FE4FFD51FC8269FD" box="[509,837,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Pogonomyrmex vermiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
usually has a smooth and shining first gastral tergum or occasionally with striae along the base of the segment, but the anterior portion of the first gastral tergum is never coriarious as occurs in 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FE10FC99FDC46835" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kusnezov" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[418,515,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FE10FC99FDC46835" box="[418,515,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FDA1FC99FCC86835" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kusnezov" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[531,783,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FDA1FC99FCC86835" box="[531,783,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Pogonomyrmex leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FC58FC99FB516835" authorityName="Kusnezov" authorityYear="1951" box="[1002,1174,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FC58FC99FB516835" box="[1002,1174,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as both have a similar head shape and rugae patterning. However, 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FD33FCC5FD276851" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kusnezov" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[641,736,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FD33FCC5FD276851" box="[641,736,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having an orange-red head and black mesosoma and gaster, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FEFFFCE1FE3F688D" authorityName="Kusnezov" authorityYear="1951" box="[333,504,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FEFFFCE1FE3F688D" box="[333,504,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a black head and mesosoma and a dark orangish gaster. This species was not collected by the author such that it appears to be uncommon and/or it occurs less accessible areas of central southern 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FF25FC29FECE68C5" box="[151,265,943,969]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Patagonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="103" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Patagonia</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D8310761FFADA479FF75FC55FC436FC9" blockId="103.[151,1437,151,1365]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FF75FC55FE0568E1" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kusnezov" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[199,450,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FF75FC55FE0568E1" box="[199,450,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Pogonomyrmex leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation id="68E60D3CFFADA479FE78FC55FC476FC9" collectorName="Thus, I" country="Argentina" county="These" location="central Santa Cruz" municipality="The" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-worker="1" typeStatus="syntype">
is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="0735B9C3FFADA479FD6EFC55FCF468E1" box="[732,819,979,1005]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">syntype</typeStatus>
series of 
<specimenCount id="CE88CCE8FFADA479FC11FC55FBF668E1" box="[931,1073,979,1005]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" type="worker">five workers</specimenCount>
collected in 
<location id="DD5151BAFFADA479FB76FC55FA5F68E1" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:5027B677FFAFA479FF25FEA1FE786E59:DD5151BAFFADA479FB76FC55FA5F68E1" box="[1220,1432,979,1005]" country="Argentina" county="These" municipality="The" name="central Santa Cruz" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">central Santa Cruz</location>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A09947F1FFADA479FF25FC71FECD6F1D" box="[151,266,1015,1041]" name="Argentina" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingMunicipality id="38559D1BFFADA479FEA7FC71FE866F1D" box="[277,321,1015,1041]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">The</collectingMunicipality>
range of variation in the species is unknown given the few workers that were collected in the type series, but several morphological characters make this a distinct taxon. 
<collectingCounty id="31507FEDFFADA479FC7AFB9DFBCC6F39" box="[968,1035,1051,1077]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">These</collectingCounty>
characters include: (1) ferruginous orange to orange-red head and black mesosoma and gaster, (2)&gt; 12–15 weak, irregular, longitudinal rugae on the promesonotum that continue to the anterior margin of the pronotum, (3) long superior propodeal spines, and (4) first gastral tergum moderately to strongly coriarious over the basal area to the anterior one-third or more of segment. 
<collectorName id="757B62B7FFADA479FF25FB2DFF216FC9" box="[151,230,1195,1221]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Thus, I</collectorName>
elevate 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FEF6FB2DFE656FC9" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kusnezov" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[324,418,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FEF6FB2DFE656FC9" box="[324,418,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from subspecies to rank as a valid species
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="909454EAFFADA479FF75FB48FE786E59" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="D8310761FFADA479FF75FB48FE786E59" blockId="103.[151,1437,151,1365]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FF75FB48FEE06FE4" bold="true" box="[199,295,1230,1256]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Biology.</emphasis>
Nothing is known about the biology of 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FD5CFB49FC896FE5" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kusnezov" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[750,846,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonis">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FD5CFB49FC896FE5" box="[750,846,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">P. leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it is only known from the 
<typeStatus id="0735B9C3FFADA479FB2FFB49FB0A6FE5" box="[1181,1229,1231,1257]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">type</typeStatus>
series, which was collected about 70 years ago. The 
<typeStatus id="0735B9C3FFADA479FDA3FB75FD866E01" box="[529,577,1267,1293]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">type</typeStatus>
locality is likely at an elevation of 
<quantity id="1F76AA84FFADA479FC74FB75FB826E01" box="[966,1093,1267,1293]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" unit="m" value="450.0" valueMax="600.0" valueMin="300.0">300–600 m</quantity>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FB3DFB75FA976E01" authority="Steppe" authorityName="Steppe" box="[1167,1360,1267,1293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Patagonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Patagonia Steppe</taxonomicName>
ecoregion, as defined by 
<bibRefCitation id="BC1F7A90FFADA479FEC5FA91FD8A6E3D" author="Olson, D. M. &amp; Dinerstein, E. &amp; Wikramanayake, E. D. &amp; Burgess, N. D. &amp; Powell, G. V. N. &amp; Underwood, E. C. &amp; D'Amico, J. A. &amp; Itoua, I. &amp; Strand, H. E. &amp; Morrison, J. C. &amp; Loucks, C. J. &amp; Allnutt, T. F. &amp; Ricketts, T. H. &amp; Kura, Y. &amp; Lamoreux, J. F. &amp; Wettengel, W. W. &amp; Hedao, P. &amp; Kassem, K. R." box="[375,589,1303,1329]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" pagination="933 - 938" refId="ref148173" refString="Olson, D. M., Dinerstein, E., Wikramanayake, E. D., Burgess, N. D., Powell, G. V. N., Underwood, E. C., D'Amico, J. A., Itoua, I., Strand, H. E., Morrison, J. C., Loucks, C. J., Allnutt, T. F., Ricketts, T. H., Kura, Y., Lamoreux, J. F., Wettengel, W. W., Hedao, P. &amp; Kassem, K. R. (2001) Terrestrial ecoregions of the world: a new map of life on Earth. Bioscience, 51 (11), 933 - 938. https: // doi. org / 10.1641 / 0006 - 3568 (2001) 051 [0933: TEOTWA] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Olson 
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFADA479FE70FA91FE336E3D" box="[450,500,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">et al</emphasis>
. (2001)
</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation id="40B51BE4FFADA479FDEFFA91FD256E3D" box="[605,738,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="94.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[420,1165,181,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-19@94.[420,1167,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="94" captionText="FIGURE 43. Geographic distribution of: (A) Pogonomyrmex intermedia, (B) P. lagunabravensis, and (C) P. leonis. The large black circle in each panel denotes the type locality." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499251" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5499251/files/figure.png" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Figure 43C</figureCitation>
). This species most likely inhabits the vast, difficult to access central areas of 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFADA479FEFBFABDFE7C6E59" box="[329,443,1339,1365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Patagonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="103" pageNumber="170" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Patagonia</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
